Key Concepts-

    Shared Network Stack: Explain that even though these are two different containers with their own filesystems, they share the same network interface (lo).

    Port Conflicts: Mention that if both containers tried to listen on port 80, the Pod would fail to start (CrashLoopBackOff) because the port is already bound within that shared namespace.

    Performance: Since traffic stays within the same network namespace, there is virtually zero latency and no network overhead (it doesn't even hit the Flannel/VXLAN bridge).
